cription":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Yes—mocking/stubbing summary text cannot detect factual misrepresentation. REAL-INFRA: External infra is not the main boundary; model output quality is. MOCK-HIDE: A mocked model would always pass and hide hallucination/omission failures. LLM-DEP: Yes—correctness depends on real model judgment/generation and can vary run-to-run. MULTI-STEP: No—single summary-generation step.","test_description":"Run the real summary-generation model on fixed input fixtures with known key values, then score output against a factuality rubric (required values present, no contradictory numbers, no invented incidents). Use repeated runs/tolerance bands to account for nondeterminism while still failing real misrepresentation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Yes—mocked SMTP/email APIs can miss auth, TLS, routing, and formatting issues. REAL-INFRA: Yes—requires real networked services and mailbox delivery behavior. MOCK-HIDE: End-to-end delivery failures are commonly hidden by mocked mail clients. LLM-DEP: Not primary for this behavior boundary. MULTI-STEP: No full agent session requirement.","test_description":"Run the scheduled script end-to-end in a test environment using real source endpoints (or staging equivalents), generate the report, send via real email service, and assert the configured test mailbox receives the message with expected subject/body/attachments.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Yes—in-process mocks may miss filesystem permission/path/timing and scheduler interaction failures. REAL-INFRA: Yes—depends on local filesystem durability plus scheduler/run-boundary behavior and network unreachability condition. MOCK-HIDE: Mocked email/file layers can falsely pass retry persistence logic. LLM-DEP: No. MULTI-STEP: No AI workflow dependency.","test_description":"Trigger one real run with email endpoint intentionally unreachable; verify report artifact is written to expected local path. Trigger the next scheduled run (or equivalent real scheduler invocation), restore email service, and verify queued report is retried and delivered successfully.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.05}}]}
